text: Cleveland is an area in the North of Yorkshire, England. That means it is in North East England. As a non-metropolitan county it existed between 1 April 1974 and 31 March 1996. The districts which made up the county are now all unitary authorities. == References == Category:1974 establishments in England Category:1996 disestablishments in England Category:Historic counties of England Category:North East England
